{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And eventually, we could actually hear the artillery and the guns, which turned out to be the British army.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was at that time that we were first sent to-- all the people in the star camp were sent for a shower.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Again, we did have occasional showers, no gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Incidentally, if I can just interrupt for one moment there, Judith, my daughter-- when I say I haven't been affected by the Holocaust at all, she says she has been affected by it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She worries every time she goes under a shower.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, I'm-- I'm terrified to hear that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never, ever thought about that, about being worried about going under a shower.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, by the by, we did have our showers in-- in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And on the 9th of April, all the people that were left in the star camp were-- were walked back to the railway siding kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And those people who couldn't walk, maybe like the orphanage people, Birnbaum and them, they were probably transported by truck, I think, to the railway siding.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were going to be evacuated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean we were amazed-- kind of thing-- that the Germans should still persist in this idea of wanting to exchange us and keep us, and not wanting to fall us into Allied hands, because that's basically what it was.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So on the 9th of April, we went to the railway sidings and put into-- there were three trains there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we went into the third train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the 10th of April, we left there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you know where you were going to?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we didn't know where we were going to.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
